      "content": "## Tips on how you can transfer your creative skills to real games\n\n- Most Fortnite players have a lot of skill against random people in a creative game but it doesn’t transfer to in-game fights. Take creative more seriously and in fights pretend that if you die you’ve lost a game in a cash cup. Then you start playing more confidently in game.\n- Don’t play fully aggressive in creative games because you definitely won’t in cash cup or in pubs, whether you're a noob or a pro.\n- Play every creative game like a ranked game, and remember that the more practice isn't always better, as for your practice you need to be working on things you are not as good at, instead of just wasting time practicing thing you know you are already good at.\n- Don't do flashy retakes or stuff in creative that you won't do in real game it's highly unrealistic since it's wasting mats, editing too fast and losing real concentration, and toxicity (flexing, emoting, etc. Instead, you should play more Ranked and Scrims to get more realistic practice.\n- Play on high delay maps or maps that have similar delay to battle royale",
