      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "- **Creative ≠ Real Games**\n  - Creative helps you build mechanics, muscle memory, and confidence — but it doesn’t teach you game sense, rotations, storm management, or pressure handling.      That’s where real games come in.\n- **You Need Experience**\n  - Mechanics alone won’t win you games.  \n  - Game awareness, timing, positioning, and decision-making are built through repetition and trial & error in real match settings.  \n  - You have to put yourself in uncomfortable, real-game situations repeatedly until you get comfortable.  \n  - You don’t “get better” by avoiding the hard parts — you improve by facing them.\n- **Play More Realistic Practice**\n   - Zone wars with moving zones  \n   - Scrims and custom games  \n   - VOD review + replays  \n- **Train Smart, Not Just Hard**\n   - Warm up in creative  \n   - Then play at least 5-10 real games daily, focusing on playing smart, rotating well, and not just W-keying like Creative  \n- **Track Your Mistakes**\n   - Did you die because of aim, or bad position?  \n   - Were you tunnel visioned?  \n   - Did you overbuild and run out of mats?",
